org.cytoscape.cyGraph.algorithms.api
Interface GraphAlgorithms

public interface GraphAlgorithms

GraphAlgorithms is the primary interface providing access to a number of graph algorithms. These include breadth first search, depth first search, Bellman-Ford, Dijkstra, Floyd-Warshall, Prim, Kruskal, Pagerank and HITS.

Author:
Jimmy

getPageranks

PagerankResults getPageranks(org.cytoscape.model.CyNetwork network,
                             WeightFunction function,
                             boolean directed,
                             double probability,
                             double epsilon)
Computes the pagerank of CyNodes in a CyNetwork with the probability and epsilon value provided by the user.

Parameters:
network - CyNetwork containing the nodes for which the user wants to compute pagerank scores.
function - WeightFunction mapping each edge to a weight.
directed - True if the network is to be treated as directed and false otherwise.
probability - Probability value alpha to be used in the computation of pagerank scores. The default is 0.85.
epsilon - Epsilon value to be used in pagerank computation. The default is 0.001.
Returns:
An instance of PagerankResults that provides methods to access the pagerank score.
See Also:
Pagerank algorithm
